NAME
    DBIx::Class::InflateColumn::DateTime::Duration - Auto create
    DateTime::Duration objects from columns

SYNOPSIS
      use DBIx::Class::InflateColumn::DateTime::Duration;

DESCRIPTION
    Load this component and then declare one or more columns as URI columns.

      package Holiday;
      __PACKAGE__->load_components(qw/InflateColumn::DateTime::Duration Core/);
      __PACKAGE__->add_columns(
          length => {
              datatype      => 'varchar',
              size          => 255,
              is_nullable   => 1,
              is_duration   => 1,
          },
      );

    Then you can treat the specified column as a DateTime::Duration object.

    print 'days: ', $holiday->length->delta_days, "\n"; print 'hours: ',
    $holiday->length->delta_hours, "\n";

SEE ALSO
    DateTime::Duration, DBIx::Class::InflateColumn, DBIx::Class.

